  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Draw Circles",
      "body": "First up, grab your two scrap pieces of wood and using a protractor, draw a circle on each piece. Get as close as you can to the edge without going over.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/9bc3a016d239a0d6.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cut Circles",
      "body": "Now, cut the circles out with a jigsaw. I clamped mine to my work table, with half hanging over the edge, and rotated as I went.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/f1e0beefc77058de.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Sand",
      "body": "Now, give those circles a sanding!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/3fa24f811d42cd67.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Apply Finish",
      "body": "Go ahead stain or paint however you'd like.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e31258a3d31438d6.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Hardware",
      "body": "Just about done! Once your finish is dry, add one flange to each of your circles. Attach to the center using your drill and 3/4\" screws.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/ddd245a0c01d0e8d.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Pipe",
      "body": "Go ahead and screw the pipe into each flange and you're done!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0853d1fb36b3b78b.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Enjoy!",
      "body": "Great work! What will you use your DIY Rustic Stand for?",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1f18b8516a976740.webp"
    }
  ],
